Will I succeed in skating this year?

A few years ago we got our dog as a holiday gift. Seeing her in the snow was the best, she loves it. Now she's almost four and I almost typed this up to say we got her last year, it went so fast.
Making snow angels and snowmen with my sister. Sledding down the biggest hill in our neighborhood.
Making a snowman with my german shepherd dog. He was rolling the ball in the snow with his front legs.

I only have one memory of Christmas being magical. We had the entire family at my mom’s apartment and I got my Barbie for the first time ever. I was so excited cause I had bugged my mom for soooooo long to have one.
I never liked the cold but I have a lovely memory of watching my sister playing in the snow, through the window, as I sat reading on the window seat in the warmth!
I was from a big family and our neighbors were also a large family. We would build our fort out of snow and have a snowball fight. We were out there till nighttime. It was the best!
Every year we buy or make 1 new ornament for the tree. I love that. Our tree does not have designer-matched sets but live & memories.
Watching my mom try to save a frozen turkey on the ferry: she dropped it, the deck was slick, and it was like a bizarre hockey game, her trying to keep this giant bird from going into the river.
Going outside at night with my sister after a really big snow and seeing how quiet it was.
Snow Class! We made this trip to Switzerland in Maloya with my school friends. I was 12 years old.
We used to try to make an ice rink for skating. It was so much fun. We never did get one big enough to use actual skates, but we would slide across in our boots.
We used to go around with a sled to bring home the Christmas tree.
I loved going outside at night when it was a full moon. It was so quiet, and peaceful and everything looked so beautiful when it was lit up by the moon. Everything glowed in the dark.
We always made snowmаn on Christmas night. The weather was very cold but we were happy with the snow.
Riding my push bike through snow and over icy ponds. So much fun sliding a bicycle at speed across ice.
It was when my dad brought me and my sister to school on a sled instead of walking to school when it was a snowy day. Then we would go to the local park and play snowball fights with the other kids!
Spending time with my grandparents. Playing in the snow, making snow angels.
One winter, me & my 3 cousins met up to play outside. We made tunnels, snow angels, and igloo houses all in one day so we could meet up again the next day to continue to play.
It doesn't snow here very often but when I was in kindergarten it did enough for us to make a 2-foot-tall snowman. It was still full of muddy water and debris from the storms but it was so much fun.
Going sledding with my parents, and when my mom went down the hill our dog ran after and tried to jump in with her.
We don’t have snow where I live but I used to love skating over frosty, icy grass in my sneakers and seeing the trails I left behind …. and usually ending up on my behind!
We had one winter with so much snow.. we lived in our own house..so my uncle and granny built for me deep and long snow tunnels in the backyard.. we played there together…best childhood memory!
Making homemade Christmas ornaments with my mom.
My friends and I used to toboggan down a steep mountain together, whether we fell over or made it down safely, we had a lot of fun doing it. We were half frozen, but that didn't matter!
Making snowmen with my sisters. Decorating for Christmas every year as a family!
I remember the time, we had a huge Christmas tree and opened presents my grandpa could not wait open his presents and my sister's chipmunks CDs we listen to it.
Christmas party at kindergarten, then home through a fresh pack of snow and a huge orange that smelled so delicious.
Shopping in town with my mom and looking at the Christmas lights & holiday window displays. We'd stop for lunch & discuss the beautiful window displays and then stop for cocoa & pie on our way home.
We don't have winter in Indonesia, but I loved Christmas since I was little! December is my fav month because my birthday is on the 20th of December, 5 days before Christmas.
We loaded up the car with blankets, coffee, and cocoa and went stargazing at the former airfield site. It was pitch black everywhere and the winter sky was so clear that I could see many stars!
Snowboarding with my bf on Christmas when it snowed and making snow angels and snowball fights.
Sledding down the hill. Making snowman and drinking hot cocoa.
A rare White Christmas and being allowed to go outside and play with my best present of a big toy honey-coloured bunny.
Sliding down the hill in front of my house.
Christmas with family and making a snowman.
We were waiting for the Santa parade to go by and we get bored so we did snow angels in the sand because we had no snow in Puerto Rico.
When it was snowing my mum would go outside with me and we would make snowman and throw snowballs at each other.

We had a new year party at elementary school every year and had to wear fancy dresses & do makeup. That time, there were no blushes. So my aunt always used her red lipstick and draw circle to get that blush haha.

I remember when I was young... riding a sleigh... walking around the neighborhood... my butt was freezing at that time xD
Ah, wanna go back to those days..!
I don't know when it was, but sometime in the past, I remember climbing a snowy mountain, taking pictures of the top, and having fun riding down a fertilizer bag.
When I was young, the winters here were so cold... The one I remember to this day is when I used to eat Korean fish-shaped bread with sweet red beans and sweet potatoes in winter...
I remember the bag of hotteok (sweet pancake) my dad bought me on the way home from work. It was delicious!
When I was in elementary school, I went skating with a friend at the ice rink in the Children's Park. S.E.S's Dreams Come True came out as BGM! Can't believe Aespa is doing a remake...

It snowed heavily at night when I was young, and there was a lot of snow outside. There were no cars or people, and the ground was all white. The scenery with the snow falling in the light of the street lights was so pretty and like a fairy tale. I remember going out alone at dawn and leaving footprints.

Santa came to kindergarten and gave me a ladybug pencil sharpener as a Christmas gift and I cherished it so much that I even carried it to my relative's house. My cousin (we were like Tom and Jerry) sprayed Insecticide Spray on it, and I was very angry. Oops, not a dearest memory haha xD

In the winter, I always stayed at a cottage in the mountains. When I looked out the window, there was nothing but pure white snow, and the place was full of firewood smell. Miss the doggie that lived in that house back then ...
I remember the day when Mom said “It snowed!” and woke me up by opening the curtains.
My dad turning the backyard into an ice rink and all the neighborhood kids came to skate and my mom making us all hot chocolate on the wood stove in the basement.
Snowball fights and sledding followed by a warm blanket, cocoa and board games. And of course morning walks with the dog.

Beautiful snow falling everywhere and me and my sisters played like we had just won the lottery! Sledding, snowball fights, and much love and cuddling and hot chocolate with our parents later. Wonderful times
Hot cocoа after a fun time sledding at shade side park.
Driving around with my partner drinking a hot chocolate or tea and just seeing all the work the neighborhood did with their lights and decorations.
Every winter my dad and I would pile the snow into a big hill, then carve it out to make a fort. Originally for me, but the dogs and cats took over.

When I was young, I had a lot of romantic ideas about snow. You know the feeling when you jump in the snow? Yes, I wanted to do that, but as you know, the snow in Korea is not that soft and yes, I cried and went crazy, etc. It hurt back then, but looking back, it was a memory to remember.
My strongest memory. This is when my parents gave me a puppy in winter!

When I was a kid and when we all went skiing together, the adults would go skiing, and I would lead the kids into an abandoned container shed near the mini sledding rink prepared for kids. We'd split into two teams, build our own hideouts, and play snowball fights until the adults came back.
My dearest winter memory is waking up and looking outside of the window when the first snow is falling. In my hometown, we don't get snow very often so it is still magical to me.
Our neighbour dragged us on a sled by his car (early ‘90s)

Oh no! This place is so dusty! I need to clean it up before I can decorate it!

Muriel... It feels like you've grown up so much in such a short time!

Would you like to listen to my story of that winter?
Honey, did you enjoy building our own Winter Fair?
I loved it! I'm going to make it to the end next year!!

Thousand years? Should be at least ten thousand years!

Sunny, even if 100 years pass all of a sudden one day, I will still love you with all my heart.
A hundred years! It's so long!
Thousand years? Should be at least ten thousand years!

...Wow!

Sunny, Ginger, Mindy, William, James, and Neil: You did great on this "Bright" day!
- Bright

Pardon me, I'm Ahmed. The archaeologist who wrote you recently? Is anybody home?
Oh, so sorry to surprise you. I've been granted permission by both Dorothy and Sally to locate and examine the ancient treasures hidden here in this mansion.
Huh? You mean Grandma and Mom? They should have told me to expect company!
Hold up a minute... Did you say ancient treasures just now?
Yes. You see, I have acquired a treasure map as part of my father's inheritance.
Strangely, it led me straight to this mansion. I had expected the destination be an old temple or rainforest.
You're kidding! Show me the map!
Well, well, looks like you're right. But I've never seen any treasures in around the mansion.
Hmm... Do you happen to have an old shed about? Or perhaps and abandoned cellar?
We've got a shed. But there's nothing inside except for seeds and a couple of gardening tools.
May I take a look myself? Hmm... This corner seems suspicious.
Holy lemons! What's all that? I had no idea!
Wait, there looks to be a note here. Let's give it a read.
To Dorothy, my dearest friend, and Sally, the greatest traveller, I leave my treasure here under your protection... - Omar
Omar? My Father's name? This must be it! The treasure is here somewhere!
I can't believe it was just here in the shed this whole time!
What are these other things left with the letter though? Oh... They're blueprints!
This is... Oh, my. This looks like the architectural style of the forgotten Golden City!
A Golden City? What on earth do you mean?
Look at this shape, and this structure! It bears the silhouette of the forgotten Golden City!
Guess what? While you were looking for treasures, I actually built the stairs on one of the blueprints!
My, aren't you talented? Also, your outfit is just superb!
Proper explorers clothes are a must when digging up ancient secrets!
This Golden City is a mythical place I've been studying for decades now.
It's been all but lost since a mysterious disaster wiped it off the map. All that remains are fragmented ruins, and a beautiful jewel called "Tears of the Pharoah".
But there is still so much more to discover! The archeological potential is beyond any other find this century!
I had no idea we had such cool treasure in the house!
Shall we continue our chat while installing the floor from this blueprint?
Advanced technology would have been required to produce this shade of blue back then. You can see how sophisticated their civilization was just from their road decorations!
Haha, you look so excited. And you've just given me an idea!
Why don't we recreate the golden city in this mansion? I mean, we've got the blueprints, we've got the treasures. Why not?
I am certainly grateful, but I worry in regards to all the time and effort required.
Hey, this is worth it! It's for Mom and Grandma!
Also, I'm super curious about what happened to this city!
I will do my best to investigate! Shall we get started then? Let us reveal the mysteries of the forgotten Golden City!
Wow, the fountain is flowing like an oasis in the desert! I can't believe they were able to build such intricate designs!
Now that I think of it, didn't you mention some jewels before? "Tears of the Pharaoh", I think you called them? You said they were left in the city somewhere?
Correct. The jewels were revered as a symbol of the city. They were also a very hard mineral, disaster-proof, one might say.
It was granted it's name due to how it appeared when shining upon the ruins. Many say it looked...lonely.
I wonder what on earth could have happened?
There are countless historical books on the subject. But one thing connects them all - how the Pharaoh truly loved this city.
After it fell into ruin, it made sense for the jewels to incur such a title.
Ginger! I think it suits you!
Haha, indeed! Actually, the Egyptians loved cats too. They often worshipped them as gods.
This sculpture here demonstrates the fact.
Huh. Hey, Ahmed? Is it me, or is it getting foggy?
Get back. There's something out there in the fog!
Who's there? I told you to leave the city!
What has brought the two of you here? I do not recognize you... Are you friends of the traveller?
This must be Raneti! She ascended the throne at an early age, bringing an unprecedented prosperity to the kingdom. She was their greatest leader!
Why do you continue to state the obvious? And why do you wear such clothes? They're odd.
The city looks awful. Was it not possible to mitigate the disaster?
Raneti, your highness. I have some bad news. It is actually about four thousand years after the disaster you and people so desperately tried to prevent.
How could that be? Four thousand years, you say?
But my people... Where are my people? What happened?
I called you their greatest leader before. But it was not just due to the peace and prosperity.
You, alone, remained and defended those during the disaster. That's why you are rememebered to this day as a legend.
This mural here tells the story. It was painted by the people, depicting the great Raneti, she who humbly guarded the city.
The people... At least they were safe.
Ginger, you are moved by the story?
Great mighty God, what brings you down to our humble realm like this?
I see now. My people's safety was granted due to this God's protection!
Cute... No, great, wonderful God! Stay and relax as long as you desire.
How dare you laugh in that manner before me!
I'm glad I kept my giggles low key. Hehe.
It was true that cats were worshipped as Gods though!
We can now consider it an archaeological fact. Of course, it may difficult be proving that the way we validated this matter was by meeting a four thousand year old Pharaoh...
More importantly, how and why is she here?
This is an obelisk - it seals the darkness.
It was built to prevent evil spirits from infesting the city, I think.
That thing seals the darkness, you say? My, you modern people are not that imaginative!
We had no need of such things. We had the great God to protect us!
Ginger is really soaking this up...
Raneti, I'm sorry, I don't quite understand.
This was built by the people to celebrate my birthday.
Oh no! Perhaps you could translate these letters then?
Uh... "Happy Birthday, Raneti!", "Today's all about you!", "Treat yo'self!" You get the idea.
My interpretation was not even close, it seems.
Haha! People never change, I guess!
Raneti, with all due respect, may I ask for some details in regards to the disaster?
Much has been lost to history, it seems. I understand. Even in my time, the details were kept quiet.
A traveller visited our city one day. She arrived by boat, and had red hair, like this one.
Wow, really? Maybe it was one of my ancestors!
The traveller spoke of a disaster that occurred in another region. It was strange, a bright white light that flashed and enveloped an entire continent...
She said it... It seemed as if a great time had passed in a mere few seconds.
Why do I feel like I've heard this before?
Thus it was prophesized our city would be next. I tried to prevent the disaster in secret to avoid panic amongst the people.
What can you tell us about the day on which the disaster struck?
That day... I led an evacuation of the city. I provided my people with a suitable excuse, then returned to the city alone.
I knew that if I could find the origin of the flash, I might have a chance to seal it.
The traveller had gifted me a special jewel she said could be used for such a ritual.
Do you mean "Tears of the Pharaoh"? The legendary gemstone?
"Tears of the Pharaoh"? What on earth do you mean? The Pharaoh does not shed tears! This was called "The Piece of the Rainbow". Or it was, when I had them.
I cry even when I'm happy sometimes! Everyone sheds a few tears now and then!
True, I suppose. Well, anyway, this jewel was unlike any I had ever seen before.
I risked it all to stop the disaster. Fortunately, damage seems to have been limited to just our city.
I see. Now it all makes sense.
Have I slumbered all these years to simply share my story?
Ginger! Don't hop around like that! You could hurt yourself!
Do not challenge the great Ginger God's will, Sunny...
This structure you have built here, is this a gazebo?
Yeah, that's right! There's a real pretty view of the mansion from here.
I do miss the days when I watched the flowing river with my people in our gazebo...
Did you know the gazebo actually originated in Egypt?
I found some blueprints for a gazebo in the treasure trove. Why don't we rebuild it together?
I can't believe this pottery was found in such good condition.
It was in the shed you searched before. I adore it, so I brought it with me.
Isn't it marvellous? The color, the shape...
These designs are what first drew me to studying the Golden City.
It always broke my heart to think how much was lost...
A civilization that builds such beautiful things, they must have had brilliant minds. My career started with a yearning to better connect with that.
It's just so amazing that this pottery remained intact! I assume this was an ornament of some kind? Or a decoration, perhaps?
Haha! Don't be silly. That was an exercise tool. I would fill it with water to control the weight, then lift it to train my arms.
But, I suppose if you see it as decoration, that's perfectly fine also.
Then let's decorate more in this style!
The great gazebo of the Golden City is finally complete!
Your skills are rather impressive, Sunny. If this was four thousand years ago I may have even appointed you as my royal architect!
Such a perfect reproduction... It's like a window into another time!
I suppose this one only cares for his own interests then.
I once had someone similar in my employ, a royal officer who studied ancient history.
That might have been Ahmed's ancestor! Or maybe Ahmed travelled back in time! Hehe.
It's so cool that even back then, you were still interested in the past.
One must always understand the past, if they are to prepare for the future.
Wow, a coronation ceremony! That's awesome!
How old were you for this ceremony?
What was I doing when I was fifteen?
The former Pharaoh was so proud. All the people were so happy...
Oh, all of a sudden I feel a great pain in my heart...
I will manage. Let us continue.
Oh great Ginger God, why do you like this meagre place so?
No matter where I take her, she returns to this dull little corner!
Cats tend to like small corners!
That's why I decorated this place for her... But it's far too shabby for a deity!
Haha, you're sure getting spoiled today, hey Ginger?
"Don't you dare call me Ginger. I am the great Ginger God!" That's what she's saying, I bet.
Earlier you mistakenly identified the obelisk - you thought it a tool to seal the darkness.
Yes, I remember. I'm glad you corrected me.
Well, as a matter of fact, this stucture here actually served that role.
However, this is not its final form. It was typically decorated with "The Piece of the Rainbow", a jewel you now refer to as "Tears of the Pharaoh".
The intent was for the energy of the jewels to add strength to the city.
What a shame. I would love to see it in action.
Let's check the warehouse for some jewels later! Maybe we get lucky!
I'm so proud of both of you! We are restoring the palace to its former glory!
We've just got the main body of the palace left. I can't wait to see how it turns out!
Are you okay? Make sit down a minute.
Do not fret, I will heal with ease once the palace is complete.
It's just sad that our original structures did not survive for all to see.
But we are bringing them back! And it's all thanks to Raneti's magical return.
Yes. I have waited an age for this.
Soon all can appreciate this beautiful city I loved so much.
But it is not yet perfect. We are still missing the most important piece...
The most important... What is it?
Wow, so shiny! Finally, a palace worthy of the name Golden City!
More treasures were found in the back of the shed.
I had expected this might happen. I think I must depart.
I yearned for our history to never be forgotten. With every ounce of my soul I sought to make it so. Now in light of what you have built here, my purpose is fulfilled at last...
I must continue on into the afterlife. I'm already four thousand years late, mind you!
I'll will devote myself to researching and promoting your people's history. You are in good hands with us, Raneti.
And maybe find a way to come back for a visit someday!
Goodbye, Renati. You will be missed.
Now that she's gone, it almost feels like a dream...
A dream that faded too soon...
So, I guess you're leaving too?
I'd like to stay and examine the artifacts further.
If that's alright with you, of course.
Absolutely! Not a problem at all! Just include my name on your research paper.
And I suppose you wanted to be included too, almighty Ginger God!
What a swell summer this has been!
So... Herein lies the truth about the misunderstood, Golden City...
Ahmed! Have you finally finished your paper?
Indeed! Though as it turns out, I had enough material to fill an entire book!
Then I just need to check the most important part! Hehe.
Let's see... Is this the end here?

Lastly, I would like to express my sincere gratitude to Sunny, who helped me recreate the Golden City in detail. Special thanks also to the almighty Ginger, who eased my fatigue with her cuteness. And of course Raneti, who upheld the truth of her history for over four thousand years.
All that remains is to get this book published!
I'll look forward to it! And please do come back soon!
Thank you, dear Sunny. From the bottom of my heart.
These jewels are called "Tears of the Pharaoh".
It's a bummer that something so beautiful was given so sad a name!
I bet something mysterious might happen if I rest under this gazebo!
Sharing the same space with ancient civilisations is mysterious in of itself!
The temple must be responding to the powers of the jewels!
It's more beautiful than I imagined. Words can't begin to describe...
Wow! It's a whole new vibe with that fountain in here!
The fresh flowing water really demonstrates what a vibrant city it was!
Welcome, everyone, to the party garden!
The party garden? You've already named it, then.
Nothing says "party" like weeds and dead leaves.
Don't worry, we'll make it a proper party place!
To be honest, I was actually looking forward to more renovations! It's a chance to see Sunny in her element.
Mindy, you must be pretty busy. How'd you get time to come?
Thankfully I've finished the worst of my work.
Thanks to you, the product launch went well, and Antonio's helped the ad campaign pull in more sales.
It's smooth sailing so far, huh?
Yeah! Antonio's manager even called me and asked if I could stop by.
Yeah. He wanted me to stop by if I had the time. Oh, and that you'd be happy to see me.
So what's the theme of the party, lemon lady?
It's everyone being super happy, eating super delicious food and watching super great movies in a super pretty garden!
Then let's invite the other islanders. Let's put food on one side and the screen in the middle.
I can't believe how you interpreted Sunny's words. Kind of amazing, really...
It's a shame such a huge tree had to be cut down because of how wilted it was.
It reminds me of the Christmas trees Grandma had.
She'd turn on the decorative lights, and they would sparkle like magic!
It was like I'd entered another world!
It must have been a beautiful memory.
How about we recreate that moment? We'll start the part with a lighting ceremony.
Then let's set up some cozy decorations and plant a healthy new tree!
By the way, who else should I invite to the party?
Come to think of it, I saw someone lurking around by the movie set.
She seemed to want to go inside. Maybe she's a fan?
Really? My bluebirds get news so fast.
Do you remember who she was?
Well, she was wearing a pink shawl and had red, fluffy hair. She looked pretty excited.
I feel like I know someone like that. Hmm...
Oh? She's over there! I guess she hasn't left yet.
Hey, Allegra! What are you doing here?
What!? What, what did I do!? What!?
Are you curious about this place?
Wait, you're Antonio! I've never seen you this close...
Allegra, was it? Pleased to meet you.
I've never seen Allegra act like this...
Ma'am, you're here to see Antonio, right?
I-I've been a fan of yours since Frankentonio!
That's what fans like to call his take on Frankenstein.
Nothing to be done, then. I'll invite you to the party!
Wait, aren't we supposed to be fighting?
Well, yeah, but you invited me to that barbecue, remember?
So this is me repaying you!
She didn't poison the food, did she?
Nope! It was super yummy! Mmmh, barbecue...
Oh, there's a piano here too?
That's right! Since you're here, how about we hold a little concert after the party?
Oh, can I sing along? If you don't mind.
The party's already getting more exciting!
Wow, the stage is so pretty...
I'm over the moon that we can perform together.
Oh! Because of the audience, right?
Not because of the audience, Mindy. Because of you.
Seems like Antonio wants to win her heart!
Marco! I think it's best we leave.
It's nothing! L-let's get back to work.
No party is complete without a super fancy fountain!
I've never seen one so pretty. The flowers are a lovely touch.
I suppose it's not the worst...
Wow, look at all the yummy food!
I picked them with you in mind.
That's Neil for you! Always Sunny Sunny Sunny.
I invited him since the desserts are his.
Out party with everyone eating super yummy food and watching a super good movie is almost ready!
All we have left to set up is the movie screen.
I bet it would look gorgeous with some vines wrapped around the rafters!
I can't believe my movie's being played on such a wonderful screen!
The party's about to start! Everyone get ready!
Then let's start the party with a fancy lighting ceremony!
I'm going to get emotional! Thank you all so much!
Shall we start with our celebratory performance?
I'm still anxious...but I'll try my best!
I never dreamed I'd listen to Antonio perform so close! Thank you, Sunny.
Yeah, it's a blast! I'm so happy.
It's so pretty, isn't it, Mindy?
Yeah. I'm glad I decided to come. Now I have another happy memory to savor. Good times and good people...
That's right. Our performance was my highlight. Your piano skills allowed my singing voice to soar to new heights!
I'll remember this forever. The time we spent together, the laughter...and your beautiful smile.
It's special in a different way for everyone.
Well, I should get going. Thank you for the party.
I should leave too. Much as I hate to admit it...you put on a good party.
Maybe I'll invite you again if you stop being grumpy.
Thank you so much, lemon lady. Though I feel like words can't communicate how grateful I really am...
I'm grateful too. Thank you for making such special memories with us!
I should probably finally head back home.
I don't think I would've if not for the help you've all provided. You've given me the courage to return with my head held high!
I'm glad to see Marco's happy.
It was a lovely time. If you need an investment in any future products, let me know, okay?
You can ride in my jet if you'd like, Marco. It's a long way back, after all.
Sounds good. Shall we head out?
I'll get going too. Thank you for the new memories, Sunny.
Oh, I'm gonna cry! Hurry and go before you see any tears!
Haha, understood! If you're ever in town, come say hi.
Get home safely, everyone! You'd all better come and visit sometime!
Hmm. Why does it feel sleepy all of a sudden?
Is it because of the new seeds I brought?
Yes! It's the seeds of a rare plant named Dreaming Peony.
I know! The flower is called Dreaming Peony because it looks like a sleeping child.
I can't wait to bloom this beautiful flower! Let's get gardening, Bright!
Bright! I've never seen a flower as beautiful as this before!
It feels like it will wake up soon and talk to us!
But we shouldn't interrupt her dream. Let's be quiet!
Glad I wore my coziest shoes. I'll go everywhere!
Tell me you're coming to this party. Celebrities will be there!
There will be a masquerade ball tonight in the city!
You know I'm not a party person...
You can thank me later. Bye!!
I shouldn't leave this fancy outfit unused though...
Maybe just give it a try?
Hmm, the people, the building... Long time no see.
I can finally chill out for a while.
I'll take TONS of photos if I really see a celebrity!

Huh?
Just a broken high heel, haha.
This is embarrassing.
Let me help you stand up.
I happen to have a pair of heels. Would you exchange them for your old ones?

Wow, these fit perfectly!
Thank you so much!
Have a great time!
Hey! What were you doing with my shoes?
How about these? You'll look much better.
It was a limited edition!! You better get them back later!
Oh... Are you okay? Hope you get well soon! Goodbye!
Who said I'm not a party person?
...and I notice some super famous people!!
Whoa... I don't dare to even approach them!
For me? Oh... I shouldn't have just vanished.
Haha, that's right. I wanted to be with you tonight.
That's why I got you those heels.

I'm not feeling this party.
How about one with just the two of us?

Just the two of us..?
That sounds fun!

Ugh, will he be okay swept away by the crowd?
My feet hurt so much, too...
Even high fashion can't solve the toe pain problem.
I'll go back to the hotel.
The best day ever became the worst in a second.
What, are my shoes scuffed? What's so interesting on the floor?
You're not so timid, are you?
I keep bumping into you. We don't seem to be just two ships passing in the night...
In that case... my offer still stands. Party with just the two of us?

I like your taste in music.
I would've danced to it if there was no one here.
The best part of the city is that we can hide in the crowd.
Haha, but sharing earphones still stop me from dancing!
I'll show you it's actually possible!
By the way... What's your name?

Aren't we happy right now?
No matter who we are or what we've done.
I don't want to ruin the moment.
How about we just free ourselves for once?

Hmm... Sounds fun.
And I know a game perfect for this.

It's... The Show Your Stuff game!!
Show everything you have, except your phone and wallet.
We can learn about each other in a fun way!
I knew that you were my kind of person. Sounds like so much fun!
Only that... I don't have much to show you.
But I promise I'll take out everything I have on me.
Hmm... It seems unfair, but okay!
You should take out literally everything!!
A wallet and a phone and perfume... Are these all?
Anyway, we both use the same perfume!
Really?! Right! This perfume fits well with everyone.
All I have is a car key.
(Gosh... Isn't that a fancy car brand?)
I promised you to show everything on me, so I'll show you my secret.

You didn't expect that coming, did you?
Don't worry. It doesn't smell.
It's just a little habit of mine since I was a kid.
I want to hear more about this!
Oh... It hurts... a lot, actually.
It's my bad. I should've noticed sooner.
But I made it to the party thanks to these heels!
Would you like to come over to my hotel room? Rest your legs for a while.
I want to repay you for such a fun night.
I'm in! I hope you have spare shoes.
Traffic jams seem to be endless in this city.
Are you bored? I got a small gift for you, it might ease the monotony.
Close your eyes for a second?
Aww, thank you so much! The petals are so soft.
Your happiness makes me happy, too.
...Is it okay if I kiss you right now?
Am I? I'm glad that we feel the same way.
Ah, we're here. Welcome! This place is like a home to me.

I can see the whole city up here!
I'm going to take a picture.
...but what do you mean that this is like a home to you?
To be precise, I live in hotels.
Haha, let's not ask such questions today.
I have a ton of questions, but we can talk about something more fundamental...
By the way, the layout is beautiful. I love the details.
Actually, I majored in interior design.
Wow, we're almost in the same field.
I'm exhausted, but I could talk all night with you.
Haha, really? I lost track of time talking with you, too.
How can we get along this well?
Gosh... Did I sleep here last night??
Why is nobody here? Did he leave...?
These are shoes... and a letter!
It's going to rain today. Wear these shoes and take my umbrella.
I had an unforgettable time yesterday. Call me later. Here's my number.

A number I don't recognize...
Could it be..?
You're not the only one who had an unforgettable time.

I didn't expect you to call.
City people tend to come and go.
Luckily, I'm not from the city.

Haha, I'm a lucky man.
May I take you out tonight? I know a perfect place.
The very first restaurant I came to in this city turned out to be the best one!
This is your first one? You still have a lot to experience!
Galleries are the gems of the city.

I'm having so much fun!
Oh, please excuse me. I'm getting a phone call.
Hey Sun! Let me guess. Sunbathing at the Caribbean beach?
Actually... I canceled everything to stay here in the city.

What?! And don't tell me you missed that party.
Ariana Venti was there!!
I didn't! Actually, I met someone there.... And I've seen him every day since.
I'm so proud of you!! Don't be nervous and you do you, hon!

It's my first time riding a chopper!
Cooler than the yacht we rode yesterday.
Isn't the view better than from the penthouse?

It is! ...and my name is Sunny.
Should've told you earlier.
Haha, any name's fine if it's yours.
...and I have something crazy to ask...
I never hesitate in front of an opportunity.
...and I think you are the opportunity of my life.

I feel like I'm in a movie!
...and the ring is beautiful.
We're now in a relationship that overcomes and embraces any pain.
Embrace the pain... Unique, yet romantic.
In that sense, why don't we tell each other a secret?
Do you remember that 10 dollar bill inside my shoes?
I was once kidnapped as a kid. Luckily I escaped, but with nothing.
All I needed was a little money to get home, but I had none.
I'm so sorry... So that's why you started to carry shoe money?
But I have you by my side. It's time to break this silly habit.
To lighten the mood, I'll tell you a fun secret!
I use the same password for every single thing!
Haha, do you? Let me guess. Your birthday?
You make me feel so comfortable.
Our life together will be wonderful.
Falling asleep while talking like always...
Even the fact that we're engaged can't stop me from feeling shy.
I'll be by your side forever.

...he's not here again.
What kind of surprise has he prepared this time?
I'm sorry. There's no progress in the investigation yet.
There's a high possibility of him running away. If he calls back, please do let me know.
Nonsense. I wanted to be independent, after all.
Grandma's help will only mean that I'm still a weak little girl.
The rain makes me even more depressed.
I want to leave this city as soon as possible...
She's wearing the heels Neil gave me at the party.
Was it just a part of some scheme..?
......Right. It was too good to be real. Can't handle this anymore.
I finally have this money in cash.
She'll definitely call me back tomorrow, won't she?
Will she solve the puzzle I left her...?
Alright. She was no different from those other girls.
There were letters in the lobby. A staff mistakenly forgot to deliver them.
She wrote a letter every single day we met.
Yeah, I can't deny the feelings we shared.
...next news. The granddaughter of the CEO of the nation's most prominent cosmetic brand...
Why is Sunny in the news?
The whereabouts of the scammer are unknown, and...
Hmm... the nation's most prominent cosmetic brand?
A cute romantic AND an heir... sounds like a lot of fun.
Alright. Time to stop torturing myself. I need to see her!
These marks on the bridge. Someone deliberately cut through these.
It’s a wet piece of paper. I wonder if it’s from the person who smashed the bridge?
It’s Grandma’s handwriting. But I can’t make out the wet, blurry photo next to it...
I remember seeing your grandmother’s handwriting in the journal at the workshop.
There’s no doubt this is Sunny’s grandmother’s handwriting!
Uh-huh. These blurry letters look like an address.
They’re names of the residents here.
They’re regulars at my lemon stand.
I don't know much about them, but I remember their names.
Why would their names be written on this paper?
If my Grandma was looking into them...
I should go meet them, too.
Maybe they’ll know something about Grandma’s disappearance!
Good thinking, Sunny. And I know <color=#3D3F81>Marco</color>. My father is friends with him.
And <color=#3D3F81>Terrance</color> is the owner of a cafe in town.
Then you know where to go to meet them?
Bright, would you figure out who <color=#2A2D89>Allegra</color> is?
Okay! Then who should we meet first?
Okay! Let's go to Terrance's cafe!
Wait. There's something on the door!
Notice! Our cafe will be closed this morning. Please come back in the afternoon..?!
Ugh, then let's go to Marco first.
On the way to Marco's place
This person briefly stayed at my father’s cabin once.
Oh, the person who recently moved in? I saw him at the lemon stand.
Yeah, he’s a movie director. He said he likes the island’s scenery.
Wait, do you mean Marco? I know him, too.
My father invested in one of his movies once.
It was a third-rate action movie, I think...
That’s good news. You should go talk to him.
You ruined my shot!! The sky’s most beautiful at this time of the day!
I’m shooting a scene for my next film. It was perfect until you came in and messed it up!!
Hmm? Is that you, Bright? And you brought friends!
Come on in! But you’ll have to pay for ruining my shot!!
The weather on this island is unpredictable, so I might not get another chance!
Haha, sorry about that. I’ll make sure to bring some fruit over as an apology.
These are my friends! I wanted you to meet them.

So you just smashed 'em? Haha! You're funny! Don't worry about it, they're just toys after all. I can always go and buy new ones.
Phew... Wah, that sure is a relief!
Sunny, why are so curious about the passengers?

Okay, but you can't tell nobody!
So you and Bright are gonna sneak on the plane?
What a plan! I don't know how you come up with this stuff.

But do you know where the plane came from?
Nope! That's okay, we'll figure it out!
It's from far, far away. Way too far for the police to take you, I think.
Oh no, I don't want that. My Mom's probably gonna worry.
No... Then all these tests are for nothing!
Not that, I mean, you taking your trip. I can bring you back home when you're finished.
You? Really? That whole plane is yours? You're amazing, Monkey School!

Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh! It's alive!
What are you so scared of? It's just a dumb toy!
Hey, that was supposed to be secret!

It's a secret just between us two.
Hmph, well I'm done with this boring test.
Bright, is it 'cause the test was too scary?

I'm sorry. Then what should we play instead?
Yeah! Let's play Bright's kind of game!
Alright, so I'll take these vegetables, the meats and all these snacks.
That'll be one hundred dollars in total!
Yep! One whole hundred! Best offer you'll get from me!
Are you trying to rip me off or something?

So how much then? One... Ten... Ugh! I don't know. I feel like you're trying to scam me!
Okay, okay, just because you're my regular, I'll give you my most special discount.
Hmph, forget it! Maybe instead you meet my very scary husband!
Honey! This guy keeps trying to cheat me! Come teach him the lesson, okay?
Me? What am I supposed to do?
It's your turn, Bright! Come on! Come!
I'll just watch, I think. You guys play on your own.
Why are you fighting so much? I thought husband and wife were meant to be on the same team.
Bright, is this not fun either? Did you want to play something else?
This is the Mongoose. Repeat, this is the Mongoose. We need some urgent S.O.S!
I need help! Is anyone there?
This is control, loud and clear. Something wrong, Mr Mongoose?
There's something weird stuck to the ship! It looks like a giant rock!
Please identify yourself! You got your captain there?
Your captain shouldn't be sleeping during an S.O.S!
Tell him if he doesn't wake up he's fired!
Uh oh, it wasn't a rock what was stuck!
Roar! I'm a slimy octopus monster!
Ha. Hahah! You guys are so silly!
Yay! Bright laughed! He's happy again!
I... I didn't laugh because of you guys, you know.
Haha, sure, sure! You want to draw then?
Oh yeah! I'm the best drawer!
Sunny, wasn't this tree house meant for just us?
Mongoose is our friend now, too. Why can't we all play here?
Bright, do you think I should join the Lemon Club?
You need to pass one hundred tests to join the Lemon Club!
Now, everybody, please take your seats.
Welcome to the drawing contest! Hosted by yours truly! Sunny!
Wow, Bright, you really are the best drawer!
You drew that doll, yeah? It looks almost perfect!
Hehe, thanks. Her name is Rabbit. Don't you think that she's cute?
You drew your face, Mongoose? You're pretty good too.
A dragon! Roooar! Super cool, huh?
Haha, no way! The body's too thin! He looks like a dragonfly!
It's only thin because he's flying crazy fast!
Hahaha. Okay, Sunny! What's the next challenge then?
Ta-da! This is the plane from this morning!
Geez, Bright! That looks just like a photo!
Right? Bright is a drawing professional!
Yeah. Ever heard of Venice? It's a water city. Everyone drives boats like this there.
Wow! That's awesome. You visited there?
You really have been on a whole lot of trips!
Whoa! I've only been outside my house.
I went to South America, I went to Europe...
Why do we keep talking about travelling for? We're supposed to be drawing here!
Oops! You're right! Enough with the chit-chat!
Alright! And the last challenge is...
Me, my Mom and Dad when we came to Sunny's house.
And this here is you guys!
Most memorable moment of the day, huh?
But why do your parents have horns, and these whips?
Really? It must be hard for you to live together... My parents always cancel our plans!
Ha, you don't say... Wow! Look at Bright's picture!
I just thought it was funny.
Mongoose, why don't you come check it out though?
Haha, oh yeah? That's a really good idea!
Why not? I want to see too!
You can't see till I'm done!
Fine then! I just won't play with you!
Hey! Where are you going all of a sudden?
Uh oh... I think he's upset.
I don't know... Maybe he just needed the bathroom?
He'll come back when he wants, okay?
I don't think he's coming back...
You really think we should leave him? It's getting dark outside...
He gets upset all the time these days! It's always all about him! Hmph.
I was going to show him the picture of course! I just wanted to finish it first!
Maybe it's just because he likes you so much?
Seems like he doesn't like me.
But he still plays with me, just to hang out with you.
That's not that big of deal.
It's a really big deal, Sunny.
Then what on earth am I supposed to do?
Well, friends help each other out, right?
So let's go find Bright! Where do you think he's gone to?
So, what do you think? She's a done deal, right?
Indeed. After she signs that contract, we can develop this place to high hell!
Hahaha. Country people are so naive. So easy to manipulate.
Oh my goodness, where are these puppies? I warned them to not make such mess!
Oh! You're here! Let's leave the puppies for now.
Why don't we wrap up that contract?
Sunny? Bright? Are you two up there? Don't make me come up to find you!
That's weird. The campervan is usually his favorite...
Hmm... Well then, where else would he go?
Oh! Our old hideout in the orchard!
Wait, aren't you hot in that mongoose costume?
Why not take it off? Oh! Is it a secret?
I can keep a secret. We're friends!
No, it's not like that, actually.
That's right! I just remembered right now! You never told me that secret you promised.
Oh, yeah. I guess I forgot.
Then tell me! What's with the costume?
She always said she loved these mongooses she saw in a TV show.
Wow, you must be a really good son!
Not really... It's getting dark already. Let's hurry and find Bright!
So he's not in the orchard, and he's not out here either! Where the heck could he be?
Could he have gone back home maybe?
No, he wouldn't without saying goodbye.
Let's go back to the tree house then!
Okay! Oh, Bright... Where have you gone?
Why do you have so many guests visiting?
Look, there's a boat coming in!
But only my family uses this place. There shouldn't be boats arriving...
Oh, wait, it's not coming, it's actaully going.
So who would be leaving at night?
Bright! What are you doing down there!

We can still reach him! The boat's not too far yet!
Bright! We'll come save you! Don't worry, okay?
I don't want to be saved! We're not even friends anymore!
What are you saying? You're my best friend of all time!
Liar! Go off with Mongoose instead! Play house and draw stupid pictures!

Are you crazy? I can't just jump off the boat!
Would you rather be sucked out to sea?
I'm thowing it! Ready, Bright! Catch!
What do we do? Mayday! Mayday!
I'm gonna fly this out to the boat!
But how will you get back then?
I'm taking this rope with me. You pull us in, okay?

Don't worry, Bright! Sunny will save you!
So stupid! Why would you do that!
Oh no... Sunny is drowning, and it's all because of me...
Bright! Come on! Get it together! You got anything there that floats?
Bright! The boat's drifitng too far away!
What am I supposed to do?
Sunny! I got you! Open your eyes!
Bright! Can you reach the rope?
Tie the rope round your wrist!
That's it! Good job! Now hold tight onto Sunny!
Bright jumped in and saved you.
I just did what Mongoose said. He's the one you should be thanking.
Bright, you're the one that actually jumped in and saved her!
When did you even learn to swim? I thought that you were afraid of water?
I just... I thought you were going to drown.
Bright got so brave all of a sudden!
But I couldn't climb the rope. I cried back in the maze...
So I was brave then, and you were brave now!
Look at us! We're even complimenting right now!
I don't think so... Your best friend is Mongoose...
And don't think we're all fixed!

I don't even want it! I'm sick of Mongoose Troop!
Whoa... King Mongoose is taking off the mask!
How about instead of Mongoose Troop, you just be friends with me?
Urgh, you're such a little pain in the butt!

See ya, Mongoose! It was fun!
Mom, can I invite my new friends to come and visit sometime?

Trouble? Why? I've just been playing with friends?
Oh, that's my drawing! Why do you have it though?

Urgh! I only get more angry the more I think about it!

And Neil! I thought I told you to take off that silly costume!
You don't like mongooses no more?
How can I when you behave this way?

Bright, why don't we keep these badges in the piggy bank?
Well, you know, you can't spend any badges. The piggy bank will always have a jingle. Heheh.
Haha! Sure, sounds like a plan.
We should get going. It's late!
Yeah, I guess that you're right. See you tomorrow then!
Geez... It's so dark in here. Where did she leave that Rabbit?
That's right, there was a flash light in the bag!
These papers are all over the floor...
Those two left such a mess behind. They must have been really rushing.
I guess it was fun that Mongoose King came...
